    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the precautionary principle seems like it's mostly used to justify slowing things down by default though. if we strictly follow that, don't we basically just grant the government the power to stop any innovation they don't like? wouldn't a more rational approach be to focus on tangible harms rather than hypothetical doomsday scenarios?",
